<li>It has been demonstrated that gdhA is repressed by Nac - s h r in `` E-c-e-ichia coli 19,101 , altho√ºgh this repression seems less straightforward than in K. aerogenes .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11814655" target="_blank">11814655</a>]<br></li>
<li>In fact , gdhA is repressed by Nac , with repression relieved in high [ NH + 4 ] , while neither glnA nor gltBD appear to respond substantially to Nac [ 17,44,45 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17233899" target="_blank">17233899</a>]<br></li>
<li>Discussion In the course of this work , nacEc gene was identi - cents ed and it was suggested that Nac is involved in GDH repression [ 12 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9785451" target="_blank">9785451</a>]<br></li>
<li>As has been suggested for K. aerogenes , the repression of GDH through Nac may allow GS to assimilate ammonium preferentially when it is scarce .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9785451" target="_blank">9785451</a>]<br></li>
<li>As shown in Fig. 8 , Nac exerts ¬™ 10-fold repression of serA in strain BK when grown on nitrogenrich media containing serine and glycine , as measured by b-galactosidase activity expressed from the Mu d1 insertion in serA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123449" target="_blank">12123449</a>]<br></li>
<li>As Nac levels are much higher in strains BK than in L * , repression of serA was also expected to be much greater .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123449" target="_blank">12123449</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the Ntr constitutive strains , Nac was expressed about twice as strongly as in strain L * and provided ¬™ 10-fold repression of serA expression ( Fig. 8 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123449" target="_blank">12123449</a>]<br></li>
<li>Nac repression of serA expression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123449" target="_blank">12123449</a>]<br></li>
<li>Nac-mediated repression of serA The serine or glycine requirement of strains with high Nac Discussion Our experiments demonstrate an unexpected link between the regulation of nitrogen assimilation and the regulation of central metabolism in E. coli .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123449" target="_blank">12123449</a>]<br></li>
<li>Our studies did not address whether this repression is directly by Nac binding to the serA promoter or caused by Nac-mediated activation of a serA repressor .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12123449" target="_blank">12123449</a>]<br></li>
